Family 
<taxonomicName box="[246,363,762,788]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hebridae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,833,966]" box="[151,430,833,858]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">
<taxonomicName authority="Fallen" authorityName="Fallen" box="[151,430,833,858]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[151,327,833,857]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">Hebrus pusillus</emphasis>
(Fallén)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,833,966]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">
On moist soil at the edges of shorelines of lakes and rivers, in wet mosses in wetlands, on the surface of quiet waters and on floating leaves of plants near the shore (
<bibRefCitation author="Kanyukova" box="[777,977,905,930]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" refString="Kanyukova, E. V. (2006) Aquatic Heteroptera (Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha) fauna of Russia and neighboring regions. Russian Academies of Sciences of the Far East, Dal'nauka, Vladivostok, pp. 297. [Kaнюkova, I. V. (2006) Vodныi poлuziсtkokрылыi нaсikoмыi фauны Рoссii i сopрidiльныk сtрaн]." type="journal article" year="2006">
Kanyukova 
<number box="[916,977,905,930]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); hydrophilic, but not aquatic; zoophage (preys on small invertebrates); univoltine; imago overwinters on land. West Palearctic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1013,1146]" box="[151,443,1013,1038]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">
<taxonomicName authority="Thomson" authorityName="Thomson" box="[151,443,1013,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficeps">
<emphasis box="[151,330,1013,1037]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">Hebrus ruficeps</emphasis>
Thomson
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1013,1146]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201">
On moist soil at the edges of shorelines of lakes and rivers, in wet mosses; hydrophilic, but not aquatic; zoophage (preys on small invertebrates); univoltine, with eggs deposited in the spring in the leaf axils of aquatic plants or in moss (
<bibRefCitation author="Kanyukova" box="[356,555,1121,1146]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" refString="Kanyukova, E. V. (2006) Aquatic Heteroptera (Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha) fauna of Russia and neighboring regions. Russian Academies of Sciences of the Far East, Dal'nauka, Vladivostok, pp. 297. [Kaнюkova, I. V. (2006) Vodныi poлuziсtkokрылыi нaсikoмыi фauны Рoссii i сopрidiльныk сtрaн]." type="journal article" year="2006">
Kanyukova 
<number box="[494,555,1121,1146]" pageId="6" pageNumber="201" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); imago overwinters on land. West Eurasian.
</paragraph>
